{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"9":{"eng-name":"Zakat (Kitab Al-Zakat)","ara-name":"كتاب الزكاة"}},"section_detail":{"9":{"hadithnumber_first":1556,"hadithnumber_last":1700,"arabicnumber_first":1556,"arabicnumber_last":1700}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":1699,"arabicnumber":1699,"text":"Asma, daughter of Abu Bakr, said :I said : Messenger of Allah(SAWS), I have nothing of my own except what al-Zubair (her husband) brings to me in his house: should I spend out of it? He said : Give and do not hoard so your sustenance will be hoarded","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Isnaad Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":9,"hadith":144},"chapter":{"id":47,"ara-name":"باب فِي الشُّحِّ","eng-name":"Disapproval Of Avarice","isFirstHadith":false}}]}